Nigeria defenders Kenneth Omeruo and Chidozie Awaziem helped Leganes keep a clean sheet while Morocco’s Youssef En-Nesyri was on target in their 2-0 win over Espanyol. READ ALSO: Samuel Ogbemudia Stadium will be Super Eagles new home-ground – Pinnick He was later replaced on the stroke of full-time as Leganes bolstered their chances of getting out of the relegation zone with 13 points after 17 league outings – two points adrift of safety. Their next La Liga fixture is a visit to Real Valladolid on January 3.